cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.MM

The paper involves computer vision techniques such as facial landmark detection, image processing, and deep learning for acne severity assessment. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses transfer learning and data augmentation techniques, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence research, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The application of the model in a mobile app for patients suggests a potential human-computer interaction aspect, making cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) a possible sub-category. Finally, the use of selfie images and the focus on facial appearance suggests a potential multimedia aspect, making cs.MM (Multimedia) a possible sub-category.
